<p>Here are all the things I&rsquo;ve mentioned in this post:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.hejki.org/ssheditor/">SSH Config Editor</a> for easy ssh configuration</li>
  <li><a href="https://cleanshot.com/" title="CleanShot X for Mac">CleanShot X</a>, the best (Mac) screenshot app you&rsquo;ll find</li>
  <li><a href="https://flyingmeat.com/retrobatch/" title="Retrobatch 2, from Flying Meat">Retrobatch</a> for node-based batch image processing and automation</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.noodlesoft.com/" title="Simply Useful Software">Hazel</a> to run any tool whenever a file/directory changes</li>
  <li><a href="https://aptonic.com/" title="Dropzone 4:Aptonic">Dropzone</a> for drag and drop operations for any file</li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/anishathalye/dotbot">DotBot</a> for syncing dotfiles and config setups</li>
  <li><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/" title="Visual Studio Code-Code Editing. Redefined">Visual Studio Code</a> (it might have its shortcomings, but it&rsquo;s so good)</li>
  <li><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/ssh" title="Developing on Remote Machines using SSH and Visual Studio Code">Remote Explorer</a> for &ldquo;Developing on Remote Machines using SSH and Visual Studio Code&rdquo;</li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/features/copilot" title="Your AI pair programmer">GitHub Copilot</a>, &ldquo;Your AI pair programmer&rdquo;</li>
  <li><a href="https://iterm2.com/" title="macOS Terminal Replacement">iTerm</a> is still my favorite Terminal app (with <a href="https://iterm2.com/documentation-tmux-integration.html" title="iTerm tmux integration">tmux integration</a>)</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.mamp.info/en/downloads/" title="Downloads">MAMP Pro</a>, tried and true local MAMP stacks</li>
  <li><a href="https://indigostack.app/">IndigoStack</a> for bare metal local development stacks</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.mamp.info/namo/en/" title="Your local DNS server for macOS">NAMO</a>, &ldquo;Your local DNS server for macOS&rdquo;</li>
  <li><a href="https://tailscale.com/">TailScale</a> for making all of this accessible when you&rsquo;re truly remote.</li>
</ul>

